/*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*\
  flash06_sweep_T --- the landing-page flash, swept.

  Same benzene/toluene flash as flash01_benzene_toluene (40/60, 1 bar,
  Raoult), but the flash TEMPERATURE is swept across the two-phase window
  by an outerDict (`type sweep;`).  At 1 bar the feed's bubble point is
  ~368 K and its dew point is ~374 K: below the window the flash reports
  vf = 0 (all liquid), above it vf = 1 (all vapour), and in between
  V/F climbs the classic S-curve while Q tracks the duty that holds each
  temperature.

  This case is ALSO the reference artifact for the GUI discussion of
  2026-06-12: "explore the effect of a parameter on a block" is not a new
  GUI mechanism --- it is THIS dict.  A future "sweep this parameter"
  button on a unit's selection card would synthesize exactly this
  outerDict (target = one dict path, range, responses = the unit's KPIs)
  and emit it for the student to author, the same way the Property
  Explorer emits its propsDict.  One sweep concept, engine-owned, GUI
  merely synthesizes + plots it.
\*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/

application   choupoSolve;
description   "Flash benzene/toluene at 1 bar: T swept 360->385 K across the bubble->dew window (V/F S-curve + duty)";

verbosity     2;          // the sweep prints one line per point; Newton detail off
